{
  "texts": [
    "Hybrid VQE.",
    "On Ascella, the single-qubit gates R(⃗ θ i), together with a CNOT gate, create an ansatz two-qubit state.",
    "We then measure in the Z-basis (using the identity gate 𝕀) or in the X-basis (using the Hadamard gate H).",
    "The output counts (grey arrows) are sent to a classical processor, which reconstructs the corresponding energy and implements a feedback loop to update the single-qubit gate angles ⃗ θ i via a gradient-free optimizer, and find an ansatz closer to the ground state.",
    "Each iteration on the QPU takes about 22 s (including 14 s of QPU time and classical communication to the cloud)."
  ]
}